description: A Chromium-based WPF/WinForms component that can be embedded into your .NET application to display modern web pages built with HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, Silverlight etc.
releaseNotes:
DotNetBrowser 1.6 contains the following features and improvements:
			The NetworkDelegate has been implemented.
			The Browser.FramesIds() method has been implemented.
			The Browser.GetRemoteDebuggingURL() method has been implemented.
			Support of Chromium environment variables has been added. 
			The issue with wrong BrowserView size with DPI 125% has been fixed. 
			The issue when TypeInitializationException is thrown on Windows 10 has been fixed.
summary: Solution for integration of Chromium-based component into .NET applications.
title: DotNetBrowser
